If you read Galkovsky's lecture on Orwell one reading for 1984 is that it's about USA taking over Britain which you can deduce by details in the book (like the currency used being a dollar). England itself is absorbed by America, but a Maoist China remains run by English Fabians.

The lectures were really good because they put it in context of the American establishment saying through "The Struggle for the World" by James Burnham that they want to run the world with Britain as a junior partner, Orwell hated both Americans and the British ruling class, etc.
Airstrip one is what the Americans called Britain during the war, launch pad 1, unsinkable aircraft carrier, etc.

Overhead press really is the one best lift, not only fixes your shoulders, but teaches you how to brace, makes your upper back and core stronger, massive stress on the skeleton to strengthen bones, it's just the exercise king. Completely transforms your physique unlike benching.

I was doing a lot of BTN lately as a main lift but realized it was making my OHP go down, I think for me the permanent setup will be doing 2-3 sets OHP and then one or two of BTN deloading afterwards... If you have a decline bench you can try replacing normal bench with it too
Just arch your back unless you're using truly insane weights or having pain it's not really a problem imo

The only mistake people do is not going too heavy and using low weights because they do it too strict instead of using hips/glutes to move their groin forwards during the press while still keeping knees fully locked, that way you can move a lot more and actually progress better
